    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-6 col-md-offset-0 col-lg-6 aha-content-right">
      <h3>The Evaluation</h3>
      <h6>A Methodical Review of a Website</h6>
      <p>Using evaluation criteria developed by usability professionals, severe problems were noted through 6 individual reviews of the site in the following categories:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Homepage,</li>
        <li>Navigation,</li> 
        <li>Content,</li>
        <li>Links, and</li>
        <li>Design.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>For example, without a responsive menu bar, the user's navigation through the site would lack structure. Features like breadcrumbs and a simple footer sitemap would be useful for the reporters.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid conclusion-section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 col-lg-6 aha-conclusions">
      <h6>Synthesizing the Evaluations</h6>
      <p>With 6 separate evaluations, the most common problems and suggestions were prioritized by the goals and frustrations of the personas. The biggest improvement for the site would come from a reorganization of the content. The redesign would improve with images, color, and familiar words. The changes in design would allow the content to be simply identified and scanned by the journalists.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

